For a browser vendor shipping to billions of devices, even $0.15 per device would be astronomical

Let me do some math:

Chrome has ~3 billion active users
Even at $0.15 per device = $450 million
At $1.20 per device = $3.6 billion

That's the scale of what Google would potentially owe Dolby. That explains why they don't do it.
